{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# WS2 — Overlay catalog + code-review prompts + move-catalog\n\n## Why\nThe base reviewer (WS1) escalates to SPECIALIST overlays; the gate also triggers some overlays deterministically by file globs/content. This story authors that catalog (the specialist reviewers drafted in the catalog comments on 9da1) plus the per-gate kernel plug-ins (verify preamble + Pass-4 code moves) the consumer seam requires.\n\n## What\n- The overlay catalog as code-review criteria: each overlay is a finder prompt with `applies_to` globs / content triggers (security, performance, i18n, a11y, db-migrations, docs, deps/supply-chain, api-compat, IaC, tests, llm-prompts).\n- A code-review verify-prompt preamble that EMBEDS `VERIFIER_RULES_SCAFFOLD` and re-grounds against the diff.\n- A code Pass-4 move-catalog: a `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA` instance (each move `{name, template, applies_when}`), e.g. extract-helper, add-regression-test, threat-model, add-migration-guard.\n- A code-review criteria registry (parallel to `plan_review/registry.py`) + a `threshold_for(criteria)` resolver and `criteria_routing.json`.\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/code-review-*.md` — the overlay finder prompts + the verify preamble + coach prompt.\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/registry.py` — criteria, `applies_to`, overlay enum, threshold/posture resolver.\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/moves.py` — the code move-catalog instance.\n- OUT OF SCOPE: the escalation union + workflow wiring (WS3); the secrets/security DETECTORS (WS5) — this story authors the security overlay PROMPT, not the deterministic scanner.\n\n## Specifics pinned (plan-review remediation 2026-06)\n- **`VERIFIER_RULES_SCAFFOLD` source:** `rebar.llm.review_kernel.VERIFIER_RULES_SCAFFOLD` — embed its text verbatim in the code verify preamble (same as the plan-review verifier prompts do).\n- **Threshold defaults (concrete):** the `threshold_for(criteria)` resolver returns `(block_threshold=DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD=0.95, blocking_enabled=False)` for every criterion EXCEPT the secrets/High-Critical-security criteria (owned by WS5), which set `blocking_enabled=True`. Calibration of these values is DEFERRED; the values live in `gates/code-review.yaml` config, not hard-coded.\n- **\"resolve via the prompt library\" observable:** `rebar workflow validate` + the derived-prompt-index drift check (no diff).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Each overlay is a contract-bearing front-matter finder prompt with `applies_to` globs/content triggers; all resolve via the prompt library and pass the CI drift gate.\n- [ ] A code verify preamble embeds `VERIFIER_RULES_SCAFFOLD` (independence/atomicity/allow-insufficient/verdict-not-fix) and re-grounds against the diff.\n- [ ] A code move-catalog validates against `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA` (load-time `validate_move_registry`), each move carrying `applies_when` triggers.\n- [ ] A code-review criteria registry exposes the overlay enum + a `threshold_for(criteria) -> (block_threshold, blocking_enabled)` resolver (thresholds start high → mostly advisory in v1).\n- [ ] `criteria_routing.json` is delivered (the derived routing index: per-criterion exec tier, `applies_to`, default posture, block_threshold) and is covered by a test.\n- [ ] The Pass-4 coach prompt (`code-review-coach`) is authored (selects among applicable code moves; deterministic render via the kernel).\n\n## Plan-review remediation (Round-11, 2026-06-29)\n- WS2→WS5 threshold-resolver handoff made explicit: WS2 OWNS `threshold_for` + ALL criterion keys, shipping the secrets + High-Critical-security keys with `blocking_enabled=False` as the default placeholder; WS5 flips exactly those two to `True`. Neither story ships values the other silently assumes set.\n\nAdded ACs:\n- [ ] `threshold_for` defines the secrets + High-Critical-security criterion keys with `blocking_enabled=False` placeholders (WS5 owns flipping them True); the handoff is documented in `criteria_routing.json` + a test asserts the keys exist\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782766362050702001,"uuid":"b54625f8-8f17-447a-8ac3-d6dd1323a5e9"}